text: Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? Błaszczak pisze, że kwestia zablokowania Paktu Migracyjnego to zasługa jednego listu prezydenta. To dobrze ż K. Nawrocki wsparł rząd na ostatniej prostej, ale to były miesiące długich, trudnych negocjacji. Nie widziałem tam nikogo z PiS czy Kancelarii Prezydenta. I tyle.

Sellin i wszystko jasne🤦‍♀️🤭 Sellin-człowiek, który zawsze mówi „niech historia nas osądzi” zanim jeszcze skończy zdanie, postanowił zaskoczyć wszystkich.🤔 W rozmowie na antenie wypalił, że Nawrocki zmieni rząd.🤦‍♀️ Nawrocki nie ma żadnych uprawnień do zmiany rządu‼️ Nie jest też prezydentem, bo do dzisiaj jego wyboru nie potwierdził niezależny sąd, nie znamy wyniku głosowania, wiemy tylko o licznych fałszerstwach wyborczych‼️😡 Następna paskudna postać....🤢 #PiSowskieSzuje

Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

Bertold Kittel mocno o przeszłości Karola Nawrockiego !!! "Niemożliwe, żeby nie zdawał sobie sprawy" To jest pewien towarzyski układ, w którym wszyscy wszystko wiedzą — mówi w "Kulisach Spraw" Bertold Kittel, pytany o to, czy Karol Nawrocki zdawał sobie sprawę, czym zajmował się Olgierd L. Jak twierdzi dziennikarz TVN24 i autor książki "Sutenerzy Trójmiasta", L. rządził trójmiejskim półświatkiem i opłacał pieniędzmi pochodzącymi z biznesu sutenerskiego patriotyczne imprezy. Ćpun, który był kiedyś alfonsem marnuje teraz nasz czas i nasze pieniądze, podszywając się ze swoją "świtą " pod urząd Prezydenta RP 😡😡😡 Więcej o tym tutaj : onet.pl/informacje/onetwiado…

Błaszczak pisze, że kwestia zablokowania Paktu Migracyjnego to zasługa jednego listu prezydenta. To dobrze ż K. Nawrocki wsparł rząd na ostatniej prostej, ale to były miesiące długich, trudnych negocjacji. Nie widziałem tam nikogo z PiS czy Kancelarii Prezydenta. I tyle.
Napiesac wszystko mozna , a jaka jest rzeczywistosc? Caly swiat wie jaki zyciorys i kim byl batyr vel nawrocki. A te spotkania to tylko dyplomacja i tyle.

Szef prezydenckiego BBN Cenckiewicz jest w skrajnym konflikcie ze Służbą Kontrwywiadu Wojskowego‼️😡 Jego elementem było wstrzymywanie promocji na pierwszy stopień oficerski w SKW‼️👎 Wnioski leżały od maja-Nawrocki podpisał je, gdy dziennikarze zaczęli zadawać pytania, czy BBN blokuje całą procedurę🤔😠 Prezydent jest zwierzchnikiem sił zbrojnych, a SKW ochrania wojsko od strony kontrwywiadowczej, to kontakty z tą służbą należą do kluczowych dla BBN jako instytucji podległej głowie państwa‼️ Problem w tym, że kierujący BBN Cenckiewicz uważa szefów SKW za zdrajców, którzy nie powinni pełnić swoich funkcji😡🤷‍♀️ Cenckiewicz, zanim został szefem BBN u Nawrockiego, był wyjątkowo aktywny na X . ❗️ Atakował i wyzywał od zdrajców ludzi, z którymi dziś, dla dobra państwa, powinien sprawnie współpracować😠 Dla bezpieczeństwa Polski sprawna współpraca między BBN a SKW jest kluczowa‼️ Cenckiewicz, jak inni pisowcy, mianuje wszystkich przeciwników PiS agentami rosyjskimi. Klasyczne "łapaj złodzieja!" wykrzykiwane przez złodzieja🤦‍♀️ Podła kreatura i tyle🤢🤢

Szef prezydenckiego BBN Cenckiewicz jest w skrajnym konflikcie ze Służbą Kontrwywiadu Wojskowego‼️😡 Jego elementem było wstrzymywanie promocji na pierwszy stopień oficerski w SKW‼️👎 Wnioski leżały od maja-Nawrocki podpisał je, gdy dziennikarze zaczęli zadawać pytania, czy BBN blokuje całą procedurę🤔😠 Prezydent jest zwierzchnikiem sił zbrojnych, a SKW ochrania wojsko od strony kontrwywiadowczej, to kontakty z tą służbą należą do kluczowych dla BBN jako instytucji podległej głowie państwa‼️ Problem w tym, że kierujący BBN Cenckiewicz uważa szefów SKW za zdrajców, którzy nie powinni pełnić swoich funkcji😡🤷‍♀️ Cenckiewicz, zanim został szefem BBN u Nawrockiego, był wyjątkowo aktywny na X . ❗️ Atakował i wyzywał od zdrajców ludzi, z którymi dziś, dla dobra państwa, powinien sprawnie współpracować😠 Dla bezpieczeństwa Polski sprawna współpraca między BBN a SKW jest kluczowa‼️ Cenckiewicz, jak inni pisowcy, mianuje wszystkich przeciwników PiS agentami rosyjskimi. Klasyczne "łapaj złodzieja!" wykrzykiwane przez złodzieja🤦‍♀️ Podła kreatura i tyle🤢🤢

🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

Sellin i wszystko jasne🤦‍♀️🤭 Sellin-człowiek, który zawsze mówi „niech historia nas osądzi” zanim jeszcze skończy zdanie, postanowił zaskoczyć wszystkich.🤔 W rozmowie na antenie wypalił, że Nawrocki zmieni rząd.🤦‍♀️ Nawrocki nie ma żadnych uprawnień do zmiany rządu‼️ Nie jest też prezydentem, bo do dzisiaj jego wyboru nie potwierdził niezależny sąd, nie znamy wyniku głosowania, wiemy tylko o licznych fałszerstwach wyborczych‼️😡 Następna paskudna postać....🤢 #PiSowskieSzuje

🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? "Niemożliwe, żeby nie zdawał sobie sprawy" To jest pewien towarzyski układ, w którym wszyscy wszystko wiedzą — mówi w "Kulisach Spraw" Bertold Kittel, pytany o to, czy Karol Nawrocki zdawał sobie sprawę, czym zajmował się Olgierd L. 🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

Ćpun, który był kiedyś alfonsem marnuje teraz nasz czas i nasze pieniądze, podszywając się ze swoją "świtą " pod urząd Prezydenta RP 😡😡😡 Więcej o tym tutaj : onet.pl/informacje/onetwiado…

🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? 🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

🚨 BREAKING: Visegrád Leaders Reject EU Migration Pact 🇸🇰🇭🇺🇨🇿🇵🇱 The leaders of Slovakia, Hungary, Czech Republic and Poland — Robert Fico, Viktor Orbán, Andrej Babiš, and Karol Nawrocki — have spoken out together against Brussels’ new EU Migration Pact, calling it a “dictate, not solidarity.” Under the pact, EU countries would be forced to either accept relocated migrants or pay €20,000 per rejected migrant — a plan that critics say punishes nations for defending their own borders. Fico declared: “You cannot force a country to pay for every migrant. That’s not solidarity — that’s coercion.” Their message resonates across Central Europe — yet the debate remains complex. While illegal migration threatens sovereignty and security, the reality of legal migration, demographic decline, and labor shortages also challenge many Slavic nations. ❓Should the Visegrád countries completely reject Brussels’ plan — or propose their own Slavic solution to manage migration on their terms? Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.

Poland demands Germany stop its Nord Stream investigation. The topic of Nord Stream causes panic within Poland's political class. Why? FT: Sławomir Cenckiewicz, who leads Poland’s national security bureau and is a key adviser to President Karol Nawrocki, told the Financial Times in an interview that Germany should not continue the prosecutions if it wanted to align Russia policy with Poland and other Nato allies. “From our point of view, this investigation doesn’t make sense, not only in terms of the interests of Poland but also the whole [Nato] alliance,” Cenckiewicz said, adding that prosecuting Nord Stream saboteurs might serve German justice, but also “Russian injustice”.
